10
00:00:44,560 --> 00:00:50,320
Some are different perspectives to look at man and psychology.

11
00:00:50,320 --> 00:00:57,080
An example of this may be what happens in the brain during childhood and adolescence.

12
00:00:57,080 --> 00:01:02.320
- Then it is very much about how different substances in the brain affect us.

13
00:01:02,320 --> 00:01:07,320
And what happens in the brain, for example, when we feel good or are sad.

14
00:01:07,320 --> 00:01:13,880
- What happens to an individual when they are in groups or different group processes.

15
00:01:13,880 --> 00:01:19,720
- Then it is about a scientific method and how we can absorb the research that is done.

16
00:01:19,720 --> 00:01:26,200
And how we can use the results of research studies to,

17
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:30,280
Understand man both now during the studies and then in professional life.

18
00:01:30,280 --> 00:01:34,920
